Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease and flour one 9x13 inch pan and set aside. In a mixing bowl, beat together the eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin. Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; add to wet ingredients and mix thoroughly. Spread into prepared pan. Bake at 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) for 25 to 30 minutes. Remove from oven and allow to cool. Prepare the frosting by beating together the cream cheese, butter and confectioner's sugar. Evenly spread over cooled bars.